  "time_ut": 1657381180,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dcf\u0db0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dda\u0daf\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dc4\u0dbb\u0daf\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0d85\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dab\u0d9c\u0dcf\u0da7\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0db4\u0dc5 \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The Prime Minister expresses regret for the attack on journalists",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Prime Minister Ranil Wickramasinghe says that he deeply regrets the attack by the security personnel on the journalists who went to report the protests.",
        "The Prime Minister, who says that freedom of the press is paramount for Sri Lanka's democracy, calls on the security forces as well as the protesters to exercise restraint to prevent acts of violence and ensure the safety of the public."
      ],
      "title_ents": [],
